Introduction

Moon Sua is a South Korean rapper, singer, and songwriter under MYSTIC Story. She is a member of the girl group Billlie and its sub unit Moon Sua X Siyoon.

Before debuting, Moon Sua was already known by fans as a trainee under YG Entertainment. She had been training under the agency since 2009 and was speculated to be part of the trainee group that was meant to be a younger version of 2NE1.

In 2015, she competed in the show 'Unpretty Rapstar 2' where she finished in 3rd place.

Sometimes in 2019, Moon Sua left YG Entertainment after 10 years with the agency, and signed with MYSTIC Story.

She eventually joined the trainee group Mystic Rookies, who later became Billlie, with whom she made her debut on November 10, 2021 with the release of the mini album "The Billage of Perception : Chapter One".

In 2022, she was a contestant in JTBC' survival show The Second World, which allowed rappers to showcase their vocals through a singing competition.

Moon Sua became a an MC on MBC's "Show Champion" alongside fellow member Tsuki and WOOAH's Nana. Her first broadcast was held on February 8, 2023, while her last one was on November 15, 2023.

On September 12, 2023, it was announced that Moon Sua would go on a hiatus due to health issues. On April 12, 2024, MYSTIC Story announced that her hiatus was over and that she would be coming back to the group.
